public class FloatingDate
extends Date

A Date that was created without time zone information, and so should not show time zone when written to a DICOM DT (DateTime) data element. This class does not add nor override anything to java.util.Date, besides the constructors. It is used as a marker meaning that the time zone is unknown. When a FloatingDate is created when reading a DICOM object, or formatted when writing a DICOM object, the timezone used is the JVM default timezone. The default timezone should then not been changed between reading and writing to ensure coherence.
